to create an app
in your terminal: npm create vite@latest
give your project a name
select react
select javascript for this challenge
note: a framework that extends a feature of a library is called a meta framework.
eslint.config file is auto created when downloading vite. it is just a template to enforce certain syntax rules in your code, or set preset rules to your code, called out the plugins, etc
app.css will load any time app.jsx will load
main.jsx will load whenever index.css will load
prefix with "use = hooks. adds in functionality to a dumb functions
need to have one root element <></>. it can be empty just like that aka fragment or it can be tagged as main, div, section, form, whatever makes sense for you when it comes to styling